&lt;p&gt;TubeScience is the largest performance marketing agency in Los Angeles, combining world-class creative with real-time data to drive measurable growth. We produce thousands of performance-driven video ads each month for leading DTC brands and Fortune 500 companies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our creative operations function is the engine behind hundreds of ads delivered every week. As we scale, we need a systems-minded operator to improve workflows, automate manual processes, and build the operational infrastructure that enables faster, more predictable execution.&lt;br&gt;You will own the systems, processes, and operational improvements that keep creative work moving efficiently from planning through delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Own&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Workflow &amp;amp; Systems&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Own the end-to-end creative operations workflow across strategy, production, post-production, QC, and delivery&lt;br&gt;Identify bottlenecks and redesign workflows for efficiency and scalability&lt;br&gt;Build automations and integrations that reduce manual work and improve visibility&lt;br&gt;Create structured approaches for prioritization, triage, and workload management&lt;br&gt;Partner with internal tooling teams to ensure workflows evolve alongside platform capabilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Resource Planning &amp;amp; Operations&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Build systems for capacity planning, resource allocation, and workload balancing&lt;br&gt;Partner with strategy, production, and creative leads to maximize output and remove bottlenecks&lt;br&gt;Develop dashboards and reporting that provide visibility into pipeline health, utilization, and delivery risk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Process Improvement&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Identify opportunities to automate operational work using AI, LLMs, and workflow tools&lt;br&gt;Build, implement, and measure operational improvements&lt;br&gt;Create and maintain SOPs that document and standardize key workflows&lt;br&gt;Drive a culture of continuous improvement and operational excellence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;5+ years in creative operations, production operations, project management, or similar high-volume creative environments&lt;br&gt;Proven experience building scalable operational systems and improving processes&lt;br&gt;Strong experience with project management platforms such as Monday.com, Airtable, ClickUp, or similar&lt;br&gt;Experience with workflow automation and AI-powered operational tools&lt;br&gt;Strong analytical skills and comfort working with operational metrics and dashboards&lt;br&gt;Experience supporting distributed teams across multiple time zones&lt;br&gt;Ability to operate independently and make an immediate impact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Systems thinker who thrives on solving complex operational problems&lt;br&gt;Builder who enjoys creating scalable solutions, not just maintaining existing processes&lt;br&gt;Direct, low-ego communicator who prioritizes outcomes over politics&lt;br&gt;Comfortable with ambiguity and capable of driving improvements without a detailed roadmap&lt;br&gt;Structured and pragmatic, using process as a tool rather than an end goal&lt;br&gt;Energized by fast-paced environments where results are measurable and meaningful&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
